Hi ,Case (01863473) was created. To add to this case, reply to this email.=
=C2=A0For reference:DescriptionSubject: Follow-up =E2=80=93 False Positive =
Phishing Detection & Account Restriction (Previous Case #01856810 / #018463=
97)

Message:

Hello Cloudflare Trust & Safety team,

This is a follow-up request regarding my previous cases #01856810 and #0184=
6397, which were automatically closed before a manual review could be compl=
eted. My Cloudflare Pages project and Cloudflare account are still restrict=
ed, and I kindly request a manual review from the Trust & Safety team.

1. Project nature =E2=80=93 OAuth2.0 login experience & developer tutorial =
platform

The project hosted at:

login---example.pages.dev (original URL, now blocked)

https://login---example.pages.liuxiaozhen.zitzhen.cn
 (backup accessible domain)

is a third-party OAuth2.0 login experience platform and developer tutorial =
site.

It provides users and developers with a unified interface to test and under=
stand OAuth login flows.
Before the block, users could log in using GitHub, Microsoft, and Google OA=
uth for educational purposes.

This project does not collect or store any credentials, and it does not mim=
ic or impersonate any brand or service.

2. Clear Terms of Service and Privacy Policy (public and accessible)

My platform includes publicly accessible ToS and Privacy Policy pages:

Terms of Service:
https://login---example.pages.liuxiaozhen.zitzhen.cn/agreement/terms-servic=
e/

Privacy Policy:
https://login---example.pages.liuxiaozhen.zitzhen.cn/agreement/PrivacyPolic=
y/

Both documents clearly state:

No credentials or personal information are stored on the server

OAuth tokens remain only on the client-side

The platform does not collect, store, or transmit user data

The site is exclusively for education, testing, and developer learning purp=
oses

These backup domain URLs remain accessible even after the block.

3. The phishing detection appears to be a false positive

Because the interface resembles a login UI and includes the word =E2=80=9Cl=
ogin=E2=80=9D in the URL, I believe the Cloudflare automated classifier mis=
takenly flagged the project as phishing.

However, this project:

does not request passwords

does not imitate any brand

only redirects the user to official OAuth providers

is transparent about its purpose and policies

provides documentation for developers

contains no malicious scripts, credential harvesting code, or backend data =
collection

4. Account restriction

Following the automatic phishing flag, my Cloudflare account (email: oliver=
xiaozhen@outlook.com
) was restricted:

Cannot add domains

Cannot purchase domains

Some dashboard features disabled

Pages project blocked

My account is used strictly for normal development and documentation purpos=
es, and I respectfully request that Trust & Safety restore full access afte=
r review.

5. Request

I kindly request:

A manual review of the Pages project

Removal of the false phishing flag

Restoration of full access to my Cloudflare account

Confirmation that the project complies with Cloudflare=E2=80=99s AUP

Thank you very much for your time and assistance.
I sincerely appreciate your help in resolving this false positive.

Best regards,
oliverxiaozhen@outlook.com

=20

